== French ==
===Etymology===
Old French ''[[mal]]'', from Latin ''[[malus]]'', derived from Proto-Indo-European ''*mel-'' "bad, wrong".  Near cognates include Spanish ''[[malo]]'' and Italian ''[[male#Italian|male]]''.

===Pronunciation===
{| border=1 cellpadding=5
| [[w:IPA|IPA]]
|rowspan=2| /mal/
|-
| [[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]] 
|}

=== Noun ===
'''mal''' ''m'' (''plural'' '''[[maux]]''')

# [[trouble]], [[difficulty]]
#:''J'ai du mal à m'imaginer celà'' - I have trouble imagining that.
# [[pain]]
#:''J'ai mal à la tête'' - My head hurts ''or'' I have a headache.
# [[evil]]

=== Adverb ===
'''mal'''

# [[badly]]

